[
    {
        "text": "Hi, I’m Francis, ",
        "start": 6.418,
        "duration": 1.378
    },
    {
        "text": "the host of this show \"Cooking with Dog.\"",
        "start": 7.796,
        "duration": 2.818
    },
    {
        "text": "First, let’s make the broth.",
        "start": 20.439,
        "duration": 2.654
    },
    {
        "text": "Combine the soy sauce, ",
        "start": 23.093,
        "duration": 2.137
    },
    {
        "text": "mirin, ",
        "start": 26.913,
        "duration": 1.631
    },
    {
        "text": "dashi stock ",
        "start": 30.473,
        "duration": 1.757
    },
    {
        "text": "and sugar.",
        "start": 32.816,
        "duration": 1.815
    },
    {
        "text": "Stir to mix and dissolve the sugar.",
        "start": 36.745,
        "duration": 3.101
    },
    {
        "text": "Add the chicken pieces to the broth.",
        "start": 42.407,
        "duration": 2.811
    },
    {
        "text": "The relatively thin slices of meat will cook easily ",
        "start": 45.408,
        "duration": 3.828
    },
    {
        "text": "and absorb the seasoning well.",
        "start": 49.236,
        "duration": 2.284
    },
    {
        "text": "Next, lightly beat the eggs.",
        "start": 52.321,
        "duration": 2.651
    },
    {
        "text": "Avoid overmixing to create a soft and silky texture.",
        "start": 55.425,
        "duration": 4.617
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, separate every two layers of the onion.",
        "start": 63.325,
        "duration": 3.876
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, cut them into 1cm slices.",
        "start": 72.898,
        "duration": 3.553
    },
    {
        "text": "You can also use the white part of ",
        "start": 77.433,
        "duration": 2.068
    },
    {
        "text": "a long green onion instead.",
        "start": 79.501,
        "duration": 2.902
    },
    {
        "text": "Add the onion to the chicken.",
        "start": 84.637,
        "duration": 2.151
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, heat the pan on medium heat.",
        "start": 89.089,
        "duration": 3.267
    },
    {
        "text": "And cover with a lid.",
        "start": 92.99,
        "duration": 2.035
    },
    {
        "text": "When the meat begins to turn white, flip it over.",
        "start": 98.96,
        "duration": 4.301
    },
    {
        "text": "If you want to give the dish a lighter flavor, ",
        "start": 104.338,
        "duration": 3.044
    },
    {
        "text": "use chicken breast or tenderloin instead of the thigh.",
        "start": 107.382,
        "duration": 4.057
    },
    {
        "text": "When the chicken is almost cooked, ",
        "start": 112.149,
        "duration": 2.319
    },
    {
        "text": "add the mitsuba parsley.",
        "start": 114.468,
        "duration": 2.217
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, distribute the beaten egg.",
        "start": 122.496,
        "duration": 2.695
    },
    {
        "text": "By the way, a special pan called oyako nabe ",
        "start": 126.174,
        "duration": 3.101
    },
    {
        "text": "is often used to make oyakodon ",
        "start": 129.275,
        "duration": 2.751
    },
    {
        "text": "but you can substitute a small pan.",
        "start": 132.026,
        "duration": 2.885
    },
    {
        "text": "Cover again.",
        "start": 136.595,
        "duration": 1.567
    },
    {
        "text": "Cook the egg at least halfway through ",
        "start": 142.237,
        "duration": 2.797
    },
    {
        "text": "and then adjust the consistency to your taste.",
        "start": 145.034,
        "duration": 3.353
    },
    {
        "text": "If you’re unsure about the quality of your eggs, ",
        "start": 149.535,
        "duration": 3.251
    },
    {
        "text": "please find pasteurized eggs ",
        "start": 152.786,
        "duration": 2.301
    },
    {
        "text": "or cook the egg completely.",
        "start": 155.087,
        "duration": 2.254
    },
    {
        "text": "Place the ingredients onto a bowl of hot steamed rice.",
        "start": 162.209,
        "duration": 4.334
    },
    {
        "text": "Make a shallow hole in the center.",
        "start": 168.727,
        "duration": 2.574
    },
    {
        "text": "And place the fresh egg yolk into it.",
        "start": 174.061,
        "duration": 2.953
    },
    {
        "text": "We recommend cooking the rice ",
        "start": 181.099,
        "duration": 1.668
    },
    {
        "text": "with slightly less water to enjoy the oyakodon ",
        "start": 182.767,
        "duration": 3.451
    },
    {
        "text": "since it will absorb the remaining broth.",
        "start": 186.218,
        "duration": 3.234
    },
    {
        "text": "You can also top with sansho pepper ",
        "start": 202.187,
        "duration": 2.636
    },
    {
        "text": "or shredded nori seaweed to taste.",
        "start": 204.823,
        "duration": 3.318
    },
    {
        "text": "Good luck in the kitchen!",
        "start": 208.141,
        "duration": 1.622
    }
]